The paper focuses on data mining techniques and artificial intelligence research specific to the game industry, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with predicting player churn and survival analysis, which are topics related to Cybernetics (cs.CY) and Information Retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also discusses the reluctance of game companies to share their data, which could be relevant to the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves a competition, which could be related to Social and Information Networks (cs.SI).
